caption: I didn’t have a good experience here. I arrived at 3:17 for my order due at 3:20, which I ordered at 3PM, told the worker I was here and was in a bit of a hurry. I’m guessing they hadn’t even started my pizza yet (I’ve worked in the food industry before, and know how long it takes), and instead of simply communicating that with me so I could cancel the order, the worker disappeared to the back and had me wait 10 minutes past the scheduled order time for a half baked pizza. If you’re going to give a customer a product late, it should at least be cooked all the way through, and not just hot cheese on unbaked dough. Won’t be back and will stick with the Ledo’s in Alexandria.

I have enjoyed Ledo and casbah cafe next door by delivery for years. I do have to say that it’s always been hit or miss. Pizza movers was my go to delivery place down the road and I’ve been into the pizza movers location and they had great service. My only complaint was with the limited menu and it seemed like the restaurant crew was being stifled by the owners constraints. Fairly recently, the food at pizza movers went south suddenly. After that, I ordered ledo and it was the best I had ever had. Have been ordering more in more. Last week I was picking up food from casbah (med food neighbor owned by same owners as ledo) and I saw a pizza movers manager in ledo! I suspect ledo got some good people from pizza movers to help give them a boost. Anyway, I love ledo and casbah. It’s rare to have places in this area that deliver themselves vs outsourcing to 3rd party delivery, and it’s great. Food is delivered timely and hot. The pizza is personally not really my style, but everything else is comforting and good quality- salads, sandwiches, mozzarella sticks, pasta, etc. I’m about to try the baked Mac and cheese! Good job.

My boyfriend and I eat Ledo's all the time, but after ordering tonight I will not be eating at this location ever again.  We received our food and the first container opened had two hairs in it. My boyfriend was hungry and we had paid for it so he decided to eat the sandwich anyway, as the hair was just on the inside of the container. After getting 1/4 of the way through the sandwich, he found two more hairs in it!  I called to complain and the manager told me that there was nobody in the restaurant with shorter dark hair so it couldn't have come from them.  When I pointed out that there was no other way it could have gotten inside the container and food, she told me that if I wanted a refund I would have to bring everything in just the way it came, uneaten.  I tried to ask her how I could do that when he found the hair while eating the sandwich and she hung up on me.  My boyfriend called back to speak to her and she called him a liar on the phone but agreed to replace the sandwich.  While he was on the phone with her we checked the other food and my sandwich also had a hair in it!  She still refused to believe us because "the kitchen staff wears hair nets" and at that point we no longer wanted replacement sandwiches since we were too disgusted.  Finally she agreed to give us money back for the subs only just because she "didn't feel like dealing with this."  All around disgusting and incredibly rude.  Hard to say if the problem is the restaurant or just the manager (Christine), but either way we will be ordering elsewhere in the future.
